## 3. Initialization Sequence

```c
// 1. Initialize I2C bus
i2c_config_t conf = {
    .mode = I2C_MODE_MASTER,
    .sda_io_num = {{ sda_pin | default("GPIO_NUM_21") }},
    .scl_io_num = {{ scl_pin | default("GPIO_NUM_22") }},
    .sda_pullup_en = GPIO_PULLUP_ENABLE,
    .scl_pullup_en = GPIO_PULLUP_ENABLE,
    .master.clk_speed = 400000,
};

// 2. Verify sensor presence
uint8_t who_am_i = imu_read_register(WHO_AM_I_REG);
assert(who_am_i == EXPECTED_WHO_AM_I);

// 3. Configure sensor
imu_init(&config);

// 4. Start EKF
ekf_init(&ekf_config);
```

## 4. Calibration

Before first use, execute the 6-position calibration procedure:

1. Place sensor flat (Z-up) — collect 10s of static data
2. Flip to Z-down — collect 10s
3. Stand on X-up edge — collect 10s
4. Stand on X-down edge — collect 10s
5. Stand on Y-up edge — collect 10s
6. Stand on Y-down edge — collect 10s

The calibration routine computes:
- Accelerometer bias (3 values, m/s²)
- Accelerometer scale (3 values, dimensionless)
- Gyroscope bias (3 values, rad/s)
- Misalignment matrix (3×3)

## 5. EKF Configuration

| Parameter | Default | Description |
|-----------|---------|-------------|
| Gyro noise | 0.001 | Process noise for gyroscope |
| Gyro bias drift | 0.0001 | Bias random walk |
| Accel noise | 0.5 | Measurement noise for accelerometer |
| Mag noise | 1.0 | Measurement noise for magnetometer |
| Initial covariance | 0.1 | Initial state uncertainty |

